# Scope

These conventions apply when working in **`apps/web`** or **`packages/ui`** (frontend app and shared UI). They do not apply to `apps/server`, `packages/db`, `packages/auth`, etc.

# Monorepo overview

This project is a **pnpm workspaces + Turborepo** monorepo:

- `apps/web/` — React + Vite + TanStack frontend.
- `apps/server/` — Fastify API server.
- `packages/auth` — Better Auth configuration (`@innovate-test/auth`).
- `packages/db` — Drizzle ORM schema and migrations (`@innovate-test/db`).
- `packages/env` — Typed env validation (`@innovate-test/env/web`, `@innovate-test/env/server`).
- `packages/ui` — Shared shadcn/Radix/Tailwind UI components and global styles (`@innovate-test/ui`).
- `packages/config` — Shared TypeScript config (`@innovate-test/config`).

Use `@innovate-test/*` imports for shared packages. Use `@/*` (maps to `apps/web/src/*`) for app-local code.

# Web app folder structure (FSD)

The web app (`apps/web/src/`) follows **Feature-Sliced Design**:

- `src/shared/**` — cross-cutting code used by many domains.
- `src/features/**` — domain-oriented feature slices.
- `src/views/**` — view/container components (pages-layer composition).
- `src/routes/**` — TanStack Router file-based routes (routing and layout composition only).

## Imports

- Import **concrete modules** by path (e.g. `@/shared/lib/format`, `@/features/fleet/ui/fleet-table`, `@/views/auth/sign-in-view`).
- Do **not** add `index.ts` barrel files that re-export whole folders. Avoid deep barrel chains; they fight tree-shaking and obscure origins.

## Shared

- Put shared utilities, UI primitives, stores, and cross-domain helpers in `shared`.
- If multiple features need the same helper or component, promote it into `shared` instead of duplicating it.
- If you spot the same helper implemented in 2+ places, consolidate into `src/shared/lib/**` (or `src/shared/ui/**` for UI) and delete duplicates.
- **Infrastructure + primitives:**
  - `shared/db` — Dexie (IndexedDB schema, migrations) and TanStack DB collection wiring for local-first data.
  - `shared/lib` — utilities and non-UI helpers (e.g. `http.ts` for typed fetch to Fastify).
  - `shared/assets` — shared assets (images, icons, fonts).
  - `shared/constants` — global constants (roles, flags, limits).
  - `shared/hooks` — generic hooks.
  - `shared/middlewares` — auth/role middlewares for TanStack Router.
  - `shared/providers` — app-wide React providers (e.g. `query-provider.tsx`, `offline-provider.tsx`).
  - `shared/ui` — local reusable UI primitives not covered by `@innovate-test/ui`.
  - `shared/stores` — Zustand stores.
  - `shared/types` — shared types.

## Features (domain slices)

- Each domain lives under `src/features/<domain>/`.
- Inside a domain, use **segments**: **`ui/`** (components for that domain), **`lib/`** (only **`validation.ts`**, **`utils.ts`**, **`constants.ts`**, **`mock-data.ts`** — no other filenames), **`hooks/`** (data hooks) as needed.
- Any feature that powers screens should include **`ui/`** with small, composable pieces (rows, cards, form sections, wizards). **`views/`** only wires hooks + feature `ui/` + page title/outlet.
- **Do not** add `index.ts` at the feature root to re-export the slice; import from the file that defines the symbol.
- When adding new behavior, **extend the feature** instead of putting code directly in routes.

## Views

- Use `src/views/**` only for **page-level views**: one primary exported `*View` per file that routes compose (e.g. `fleet-view.tsx`, `dashboard-view.tsx`).
- Put reusable UI for a domain (sidebars, nav blocks, split layouts, role-specific dashboard panels) in **`src/features/<domain>/ui/`**, not under `views/`.
- Naming: `<name>-view.tsx` exporting `<Name>View` (e.g. `sign-in-view.tsx` → `SignInView`).
- Prefer grouping by domain: `src/views/<domain>/<name>-view.tsx`.
- **Do not** add per-domain or root `index.ts` barrels under `views/`; routes import explicit view paths.

## Routes (TanStack Router)

- `src/routes/**` — routing and layout composition only.
- `routeTree.gen.ts` is auto-generated; never edit it manually.
- Route files delegate domain logic to `features`, page composition to `views`, and may import layout UI from `features` (e.g. `AuthenticatedShell` from `@/features/shell/ui/authenticated-shell`).

## Path aliases

- `@/*` — app-local imports.
- `@innovate-test/ui/components/<name>` — shadcn UI from the shared package.
- `@innovate-test/env/web` — typed web environment variables.
- `@innovate-test/db` — Drizzle client and schema (server-side or shared types as applicable).
- `@innovate-test/auth` — Better Auth server instance (typically server).
